The printing company **cured the October 10 defective shipment** by delivering the correct Christmas cards on October 25, which the card shop could not reject under UCC § 2-508 (perfect tender rule exception for cure). Since the card shop failed to return the Thanksgiving cards as requested, it waived its right to reject the conforming goods. The card shop’s refusal to accept the October 25 delivery was improper.
